President Muhammadu Buhari has consoled the family of business magnate, Dahiru Mangal, over the death of his son, Nura. Nura died while riding his power bike along Dutsimma road in Katsina. On Friday, Buhari sent a delegation, led by Abubakar Malami, the Attorney General and Minister of Justice, to Katsina. The President said he was saddened to learn about the demise of Nura, whom he described as an enterprising young man. “My heartfelt condolences are with you at this moment of intense grief. I pray to the Almighty to bestow strength upon you and your family to bear this irreparable loss.” In his remarks, Mangal, the chairman of Max Air, thanked Buhari for sending the emissaries. The team received by Governor Aminu Masari included Minister of Aviation, Hadi Sirika; Director General of the National Intelligence Agency, Ahmed Abubakar, and Garba Shehu, presidential spokesman.